### Stream Parameter

Source: https://docs.z.ai/guides/overview/concept-param

Determines whether the API response is returned all at once or in a streaming (SSE) mode. Streaming is recommended for real-time applications.

```APIDOC
## Stream Parameter

### Description
The `stream` parameter is a boolean value that controls how the API returns its response. When set to `false` (the default), the entire response is returned at once, which is simpler to implement but may involve longer waiting times. When set to `true`, the response is delivered in streaming mode (Server-Sent Events - SSE), significantly enhancing the user experience for real-time interactive applications.

### Best Practices
*   For applications like chatbots, real-time code generation, and other interactive scenarios, setting `stream` to `true` is strongly recommended.

### Query Parameters
*   **stream** (boolean) - Optional - If set to `true`, the response will be streamed. Defaults to `false`.
```

