### Enable Streaming Output and Tool Calls in GLM-4.7

Source: https://docs.z.ai/guides/overview/migrate-to-glm-new

Enable real-time streaming for responses and tool calls by setting `stream=True` and `tool_stream=True`. This allows for incremental updates during the tool calling process. Proper handling of `delta.reasoning_content`, `delta.content`, and `delta.tool_calls[*].function.arguments` is required.

```python
response = client.chat.completions.create(
    model="glm-4.7",
    messages=[{"role": "user", "content": "How's the weather in Beijing"}],
    tools=[
        {
            "type": "function",
            "function": {
                "name": "get_weather",
                "description": "Get current weather conditions for a specified location",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "location": {"type": "string", "description": "City, eg: Beijing, Shanghai"},
                        "unit": {"type": "string", "enum": ["celsius", "fahrenheit"]}
                    },
                    "required": ["location"]
                }
            }
        }
    ],
    stream=True,
    tool_stream=True,
)

# Initialize streaming collection variables
reasoning_content = ""
content = ""
final_tool_calls = {}
reasoning_started = False
content_started = False

```
